node.text: Visit with Lucille the Eastern Screech Owl- since we had to cancel our Owl Prowl tonight @centerforwildlife is giving us a mini tour of their owl enclosure

node.accessibility_caption: A cook pulls a pizza out of a wood-fired pizza oven

node.text:
Winner, Dinner, Second Dinner! That’s how the phrase goes right?⁣
⁣
Second Dinner returns in bottles and on draft exclusively at our tasting room today. Also you have one day left to try our Peach and ‘Nduja pizza before we switch specialty pies for the season.

node.accessibility_caption: A cook pulls a pizza out of a wood-fired pizza oven
A bottle and glass of Dinner DIPA
A bottle and glass of Second Dinner DIPA
3  cups of beer ranging from dark to light with the sun setting behind them.

node.text: Sun setting on another beautiful Saturday in Maine.

node.accessibility_caption: 3 Maine Beer Company employees behind a BikeMaine banner.

node.text:
It’s the kickoff to BikeMaine Weekend with our @1percentftp partners @bikemaine ! ⁣
⁣
While @ride.bikemaine is typically a week-long ride visiting multiple towns in a region of our state, this year they doing a weekend ride out of the beautiful town of Machias. ⁣
⁣
This weekend will give cyclists a chance to explore the coast, rivers, and state parks this region is known for and for us to celebrate with everyone over a beer when the ride is finished. ⁣
⁣
@ride.bikemaine not only brings tourism to the regions of Maine that it visits, but the ride helps to fund community grants which provide bike and pedestrian infrastructure throughout the state. ⁣
⁣
Cheers to @bikemaine , the town of Machias, and all the riders and volunteers.

node.accessibility_caption: 3 members of the packaging team stand behind a pallet of kegs.

node.text:
Fueled by cold brew and plans for the weekend, our packing crew are all smiles as they finish this keg run and get ready to send our seasonal coffee stout, Fall, out to distribution. ⁣
⁣
Fall is currently available on draft in our tasting room, and bottles will be released next Tues 9/14 and head out to distribution that week. Brewed with cold brew from local @coffeebydesign , this easy drinking stout is just what we need to kick off autumn.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maine Beer Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text:
A few of our team are out in Denver this week for the @brewersassoc Craft Beer Conference. The conference is broken into 8 tracks: Brewing Operations & Beer Styles, Business & Leadership, Diversity, Equity, & Inclusion, Events & Hospitality, Government Affairs & Export Development, Quality & Ingredients, Safety & Sustainability, and Sales & Marketing. The sessions throughout the conference provide craft breweries with the opportunity to learn from and network with experts in the field.⁣
⁣
We're giving a special shout out to our Sensory Program Manager Brooke who will be presenting a seminar on Applying a Sensory Program in your brewery with @draughtlab ‘s Lindsey Barr. They'll be following the development of our Prince Percy Pilsner from R&D up through final approval and release. Don't worry we've sent beer so attendees can taste the result our team's hard work!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maine Beer Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of food.
Photo by Maine Beer Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.
Photo by Maine Beer Company on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text.
A snifter of beer sits on a bed of ice with oysters.

node.text:
Our last Oyster Thursday of the season is tomorrow 9/9 from 5pm-7pm. ⁣
⁣
Our friends from @maineoystercompany will be here sharing the best our Maine oyster growers have to offer. And stay tuned, we have at least one more oyster event in the works!

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle of Second Dinner sits on a barrel with a black barn and sawgrass behind it.

node.text:
A fresh batch of Second Dinner is on its way!⁣
⁣
Monday September 13th we’ll be releasing Second Dinner DIPA in bottles and on draft exclusively from our tasting room. Stop on in for a taste and to check out our Black Barn Program offerings and other brewery only offerings.

node.accessibility_caption: A blue postcard with a drawing of a mountain water and woods is held up against the Maine Coastline.

node.text: We’ll be open from 11-8 today and then closed Monday for Labor Day. Hope you’re having a great weekend!

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle and mug of Black Barn Program No. 24 Kölsch style ale sit on the grass next to a white & blush hydrangea.
A hand reaches from above for a snifter of beer.

node.text:
With 11 bottle and 9 draft options including 4 brewery exclusives, we’re ready to help you celebrate the last weekend of the summer.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We’ll be open our regular hours 11-8 Friday, Saturday, and Sunday, but closed on Monday so our staff can enjoy a well-deserved day off.

node.accessibility_caption: A hand reaches from above for a snifter of beer.
A bottle list including: a tiny beautiful something, Another One, BBP 24 kölsch, BBP 25 Session IPA, Dinner, Lunch, MO, Peeper, Prince Percy, Wolfe’s Neck, and Woods & Waters.
A trail passport sits amongst pine needles at the start of a wooded trail.

node.text:
September 1st marks the return of our local @1percentftp partner @freeportconservationtrust ‘s Freeport Trail Challenge!⁣
⁣
You have from September 1st to October 31st to hike the four designated trails. Get all four stamps on your passport and you will be rewarded. Adults, kids, dogs, everyone is eligible to participate in the challenge and receive some fun prizes for completion as well as be entered in drawings for some great raffle prizes. ⁣
⁣
This is the 7th year of celebrating the beauty that Freeport has to offer, and whether you are joining for the first time or have been with us every step of the way, we welcome you. ⁣
⁣
You can pick up your trail challenge passport at our tasting room, and stay tuned for the announcement of the trail challenge wrap up party!

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle of MO next to a MO sign

node.text:
A staff favorite, MO our American Pale Ale is back! ⁣
⁣
Brewed with Falconer’s Flight and Simcoe this beer is the perfect middle ground between Peeper and Lunch. ⁣
⁣
Available in bottles and on draft in our tasting room and headed out to distribution this week. ⁣
